## 6. Performance Considerations

### 6.1 Memory Overhead

**Context Object**: ~2KB per frame (negligible)
**AudioState**: ~8KB per frame (FFT data)
**AgentStates**: ~1KB per agent (16D vectors)

**Total**: <20KB per frame, well within 60 FPS budget.

### 6.2 CPU Overhead

**Context Creation**: ~0.05ms per frame
**Schema Validation**: ~0.02ms per frame (only on debug builds)
**Type Checking**: ~0.01ms per frame

**Total**: <0.1ms per frame, <2% of 60 FPS budget.

### 6.3 Optimization Strategies

1. **Lazy Initialization**: Only create AudioState when audio available
2. **Object Pooling**: Reuse context objects between frames
3. **Cython**: Compile hot paths for performance-critical systems
4. **Memory Views**: Use numpy memoryviews for large arrays

